{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775860539373,"sessionID":"ses_28677de79ffe7N05If9ptgu39F","part":{"id":"prt_d79895c88001xEYll4NVlIaMXu","messageID":"msg_d798948ca001EkzV0w1ne7yuTx","sessionID":"ses_28677de79ffe7N05If9ptgu39F","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-fefde2c40c584c85863a72801ee0de22","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-015/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-015/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-015 — PicoD 命令执行 API Proposal\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Implement PicoD (Pico Daemon), an HTTP daemon that runs inside sandbox pods to provide secure command execution and file management within a configurable workspace jail. This enables AI agents and code interpreters to execute shell commands and manage workspace files through a JWT-protected REST API.\n6: \n7: **Current State**: PicoD implementation does not exist in the codebase. The `pkg/picod` package is empty/missing, and `cmd/picod` entrypoint is not defined.\n8: \n9: **Target State**: Fully functional PicoD daemon with:\n10: - `POST /api/execute` — Execute shell commands with timeout, working directory, and environment control\n11: - `POST /api/files` — Upload files (multipart or JSON/Base64)\n12: - `GET /api/files?path=...` — List directory contents\n13: - `GET /api/files/*path` — Download files\n14: - `GET /health` — Unauthenticated health endpoint\n15: - JWT RS256 authentication via `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` environment variable\n16: - Workspace jail with path traversal protection\n17: \n18: ## Scope\n19: \n20: ### In Scope\n21: \n22: | Deliverable | Description |\n23: |-------------|-------------|\n24: | `pkg/picod/config.go` | `Config` struct with Port, Workspace; CLI flag parsing logic |\n25: | `pkg/picod/server.go` | Gin engine setup, route registration, workspace resolution, HTTP server lifecycle |\n26: | `pkg/picod/auth.go` | `AuthManager` struct, RSA public key loading from PEM, JWT middleware with MaxBytesReader |\n27: | `pkg/picod/execute.go` | ExecuteRequest/ExecuteResponse structs, command execution handler with context timeout |\n28: | `pkg/picod/files.go` | FileInfo, UploadFileRequest, FileEntry, ListFilesResponse structs; upload, list, download handlers |\n29: | `pkg/picod/health.go` | Health check handler with uptime tracking |\n30: | `pkg/picod/sanitize.go` | `sanitizePath` function for workspace jail security (symlink resolution, path traversal check) |\n31: | `cmd/picod/main.go` | Entrypoint with klog flags, CLI flag parsing (`-port`, `-workspace`), `NewServer`, `Run` |\n32: | `pkg/picod/picod_test.go` | Unit tests for execute, file operations, authentication, path sanitization |\n33: \n34: ### Implementation Details\n35: \n36: #### Server Configuration\n37: \n38: ```go\n39: type Config struct {\n40:     Port      int    `json:\"port\"`\n41:     Workspace string `json:\"workspace\"`\n42: }\n43: ```\n44: \n45: - CLI flags: `-port` (default 8080), `-workspace` (default empty → CWD)\n46: - Workspace resolution: `os.Getwd()` if empty; `filepath.Abs` for relative paths\n47: - HTTP server: `ReadHeaderTimeout` = 10 seconds\n48: \n49: #### Constants\n50: \n51: | Name | Value | Purpose |\n52: |------|-------|---------|\n53: | `TimeoutExitCode` | `124` | Exit code when context deadline exceeded |\n54: | `MaxBodySize` | `32 << 20` (32 MiB) | Request body size limit after JWT validation |\n55: | `PublicKeyEnvVar` | `\"PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY\"` | Environment variable for PEM public key |\n56: | `maxFileMode` | `0777` | Maximum file mode; reject > 0777 |\n57: | Default timeout | `60 * time.Second` | Execute timeout when request field empty |\n58: | Default file mode | `0644` | File creation mode when mode invalid/empty |\n59: \n60: #### Request/Response Structures\n61: \n62: **Execute**:\n63: ```go\n64: type ExecuteRequest struct {\n65:     Command    []string          `json:\"command\" binding:\"required\"`\n66:     Timeout    string            `json:\"timeout\"`\n67:     WorkingDir string            `json:\"working_dir\"`\n68:     Env        map[string]string `json:\"env\"`\n69: }\n70: \n71: type ExecuteResponse struct {\n72:     Stdout    string    `json:\"stdout\"`\n73:     Stderr    string    `json:\"stderr\"`\n74:     ExitCode  int       `json:\"exit_code\"`\n75:     Duration  float64   `json:\"duration\"`\n76:     StartTime time.Time `json:\"start_time\"`\n77:     EndTime   time.Time `json:\"end_time\"`\n78: }\n79: ```\n80: \n81: **Files**:\n82: ```go\n83: type FileInfo struct {\n84:     Path     string    `json:\"path\"`\n85:     Size     int64     `json:\"size\"`\n86:     Mode     string    `json:\"mode\"`\n87:     Modified time.Time `json:\"modified\"`\n88: }\n89: \n90: type UploadFileRequest struct {\n91:     Path    string `json:\"path\" binding:\"required\"`\n92:     Content string `json:\"content\" binding:\"required\"` // Base64\n93:     Mode    string `json:\"mode\"`\n94: }\n95: \n96: type FileEntry struct {\n97:     Name     string    `json:\"name\"`\n98:     Size     int64     `json:\"size\"`\n99:     Modified time.Time `json:\"modified\"`\n100:     Mode     string    `json:\"mode\"`\n101:     IsDir    bool      `json:\"is_dir\"`\n102: }\n103: ```\n104: \n105: #### Route Registration\n106: \n107: ```go\n108: engine := gin.New()\n109: engine.Use(gin.Logger(), gin.Recovery())\n110: \n111: api := engine.Group(\"/api\")\n112: api.Use(s.authManager.AuthMiddleware())\n113: {\n114:     api.POST(\"/execute\", s.ExecuteHandler)\n115:     api.POST(\"/files\", s.UploadFileHandler)\n116:     api.GET(\"/files\", s.ListFilesHandler)\n117:     api.GET(\"/files/*path\", s.DownloadFileHandler)\n118: }\n119: engine.GET(\"/health\", s.HealthCheckHandler)\n120: ```\n121: \n122: #### JWT Authentication (`AuthManager`)\n123: \n124: ```go\n125: type AuthManager struct {\n126:     publicKey *rsa.PublicKey\n127:     mutex     sync.RWMutex\n128: }\n129: ```\n130: \n131: - Load from `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` PEM (PKIX format)\n132: - Middleware: Require `Authorization: Bearer <token>`\n133: - Parse with `jwt.Parse` + `WithExpirationRequired`, `WithIssuedAt`, `WithLeeway(time.Minute)`\n134: - Reject non-RSA signing methods (HS256 rejected)\n135: - On valid token: `http.MaxBytesReader` with `MaxBodySize`\n136: \n137: #### Path Security (`sanitizePath`)\n138: \n139: 1. Resolve workspace directory (follow symlinks via `filepath.EvalSymlinks`)\n140: 2. Clean requested path; strip leading `/` if absolute\n141: 3. Join with workspace root\n142: 4. Verify `filepath.Rel` does not start with `..`\n143: 5. If path exists: re-validate resolved path against workspace\n144: 6. Return sanitized absolute path\n145: \n146: ### Out of Scope\n147: \n148: - Stdin support for executed commands\n149: - WebSocket-based streaming stdout/stderr\n150: - File deletion API\n151: - Directory creation API\n152: - File permissions modification API\n153: - Symlink creation/resolution API\n154: - Archive (tar/zip) operations\n155: - Multiple workspace roots\n156: - JWT refresh/rotation\n157: - Rate limiting per session\n158: - Command history/audit logging\n159: - Process kill/signal API\n160: - Background/async command execution\n161: \n162: ## Impact Analysis\n163: \n164: ### Upstream Dependencies\n165: \n166: | Dependency | Version | Impact |\n167: |------------|---------|--------|\n168: | `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | v1.10+ | HTTP framework; route registration, middleware, JSON binding |\n169: | `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | v5.2+ | JWT parsing; RSA signing method validation, leeway/expiry options |\n170: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Existing | CLI flag registration, fatal logging on auth key missing |\n171: | `os/exec` | Standard | `exec.CommandContext` for command execution |\n172: | `mime` | Standard | `mime.TypeByExtension` for download Content-Type |\n173: | `base64` | Standard | Base64 decoding for JSON file upload |\n174: | `filepath` | Standard | Path cleaning, symlink resolution, relative path computation |\n175: \n176: ### Downstream Consumers\n177: \n178: | Consumer | Method Usage |\n179: |----------|--------------|\n180: | CodeInterpreter Sandbox Pods | `POST /api/execute` for Python/shell code execution; file APIs for workspace management |\n181: | Agent Runtime Sandbox Pods | `POST /api/execute` for agent tool execution; file APIs for artifact storage |\n182: | Router JWT Issuer | Generates RS256 tokens validated by PicoD's public key |\n183: | Workload Manager | Injects `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` into sandbox pod environment |\n184: | Python SDK | Calls PicoD APIs for code execution and file operations |\n185: \n186: ### Breaking Change Considerations\n187: \n188: - **Auth Key Requirement**: Missing/invalid `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` causes fatal startup failure — deployment must provide valid PEM\n189: - **Timeout Behavior**: Change from 60s default affects existing clients without explicit timeout\n190: - **Exit Code 124**: Timeout uses specific exit code; clients must handle this\n191: - **Path Security**: Stricter sanitization may reject previously accepted paths (e.g., symlink escapes)\n192: - **MaxBodySize**: 32 MiB limit may reject large file uploads\n193: \n194: ### Compatibility Notes\n195: \n196: 1. **RSA JWT Only**: PicoD rejects HS256 tokens; Router must issue RS256\n197: 2. **No Stdin**: Commands cannot receive input from client; stdin not connected\n198: 3. **Workspace Jail**: All file paths relative to workspace root; absolute paths stripped of leading `/`\n199: 4. **Gin ReleaseMode**: Default mode; no debug logging in production\n200: 5. **Public Key PEM**: PKIX format (`PUBLIC KEY` block), not PKCS#1 (`RSA PUBLIC KEY`)\n201: 6. **File Mode Octal**: `parseFileMode` uses `strconv.ParseUint(modeStr, 8, 32)`\n202: \n203: ## Alternatives Considered\n204: \n205: ### Alternative 1: WebSocket Streaming Commands\n206: \n207: **Approach**: Use WebSocket for bidirectional command execution with real-time stdout/stderr streaming.\n208: \n209: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n210: |--------|------------|\n211: | Pros | Real-time output; stdin support; better for long-running commands |\n212: | Cons | More complex protocol; connection management overhead; Gin WebSocket integration extra dependency |\n213: \n214: **Decision**: Rejected. Initial implementation targets simple request/response pattern. WebSocket can be added later as enhancement without breaking existing clients.\n215: \n216: ### Alternative 2: SSH-based Execution\n217: \n218: **Approach**: Expose SSH server inside sandbox for command execution.\n219: \n220: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n221: |--------|------------|\n222: | Pros | Standard protocol; existing tooling; stdin support |\n223: | Cons | SSH key management complexity; port conflicts; harder to proxy through Router |\n224: \n225: **Decision**: Rejected. HTTP API integrates better with Router's reverse proxy architecture. JWT auth matches Router's token issuance pattern.\n226: \n227: ### Alternative 3: gRPC API\n228: \n229: **Approach**: Use gRPC for command execution and file operations.\n230: \n231: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n232: |--------|------------|\n233: | Pros | Strong typing; streaming support; efficient binary protocol |\n234: | Cons | Requires gRPC client in SDK; Router proxy complexity; heavier for simple file operations |\n235: \n236: **Decision**: Rejected. HTTP/JSON matches Router's HTTP routing. gRPC could be added as alternate transport without removing HTTP API.\n237: \n238: ### Alternative 4: Container Runtime API (Docker/Kubernetes exec)\n239: \n240: **Approach**: Use `kubectl exec` or Docker API to run commands in containers.\n241: \n242: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n243: |--------|------------|\n244: | Pros | No in-container daemon; uses existing container runtime |\n245: | Cons | Requires kubelet/Docker API access; not available from inside pod; latency for API calls |\n246: \n247: **Decision**: Rejected. PicoD runs inside sandbox pod for low-latency local execution. Container runtime API requires external orchestration.\n248: \n249: ### Alternative 5: Separate File Service\n250: \n251: **Approach**: Split file operations into separate daemon from command execution.\n252: \n253: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n254: |--------|------------|\n255: | Pros | Independent scaling; separate auth policies |\n256: | Cons | More deployment complexity; two services per sandbox; shared workspace coordination |\n257: \n258: **Decision**: Rejected. Single daemon simplifies deployment. Both operations share same workspace jail and auth context.\n259: \n260: ## Risks\n261: \n262: | Risk | Mitigation |\n263: |------|------------|\n264: | Missing auth public key at startup | `klog.Fatalf` with clear error message; deployment checklist must include PEM generation |\n265: | Invalid PEM format | `LoadPublicKeyFromEnv` validates PEM decode + PKIX parse; returns error to `NewServer` |\n266: | Command timeout runaway | `exec.CommandContext` with deadline; process killed when context cancelled |\n267: | Path traversal via symlink | `sanitizePath` resolves symlinks; re-validates resolved path against workspace |\n268: | Large file upload DoS | `MaxBodySize` = 32 MiB applied after JWT validation |\n269: | JWT replay attacks | `WithExpirationRequired` + `WithIssuedAt` enforced; leeway 1 minute |\n270: | Non-RSA JWT method attack | Middleware type-assert `*jwt.SigningMethodRSA`; reject HS256/other |\n271: | Process fork bomb | Timeout limits duration; no stdin prevents interactive loops |\n272: | Missing workspace directory | `os.Getwd` failure → fatal; `filepath.Abs` validates configured path |\n273: | Race on public key reload | `AuthManager` uses `sync.RWMutex` for public key access |\n274: \n275: ## Implementation Checklist\n276: \n277: 1. **Package Structure**\n278:    - Create `pkg/picod/` directory\n279:    - Define `Config` struct in `config.go`\n280:    - Create `cmd/picod/main.go` entrypoint\n281: \n282: 2. **Server Setup**\n283:    - `NewServer` constructs Gin engine with ReleaseMode\n284:    - Register global Logger/Recovery middleware\n285:    - Resolve workspace directory (CWD fallback)\n286:    - Store `startTime` for health uptime\n287: \n288: 3. **Authentication**\n289:    - `AuthManager` struct with RSA public key\n290:    - `LoadPublicKeyFromEnv` — read PEM, decode, parse PKIX\n291:    - Fatal on missing/invalid key\n292:    - `AuthMiddleware` — Bearer extraction, JWT parse, RSA method check\n293:    - Apply `http.MaxBytesReader` on valid token\n294: \n295: 4. **Execute Handler**\n296:    - Bind `ExecuteRequest` from JSON\n297:    - Parse timeout string → `time.Duration`\n298:    - `exec.CommandContext` with timeout context\n299:    - Capture stdout/stderr to `bytes.Buffer`\n300:    - Handle `context.DeadlineExceeded` → exit code 124\n301:    - Return `ExecuteResponse` with duration, timestamps\n302: \n303: 5. **File Upload Handler**\n304:    - Detect multipart vs JSON via Content-Type prefix\n305:    - Multipart: `c.PostForm(\"path\")`, `c.FormFile(\"file\")`, optional mode\n306:    - JSON: Base64 decode `UploadFileRequest.Content`\n307:    - Create parent directories (0755)\n308:    - Write file with parsed mode (default 0644)\n309:    - Return `FileInfo` with relative path\n310: \n311: 6. **File List Handler**\n312:    - Query parameter `path` required\n313:    - `os.ReadDir` on sanitized path\n314:    - Build `FileEntry` array; skip failed `entry.Info()`\n315:    - Return `ListFilesResponse`\n316: \n317: 7. **File Download Handler**\n318:    - Wildcard path parameter `*path`\n319:    - Strip leading `/` before sanitization\n320:    - Verify path is file (not directory)\n321:    - Set download headers: Content-Disposition, Content-Type\n322:    - Use `c.File` for streaming\n323: \n324: 8. **Health Handler**\n325:    - No auth middleware\n326:    - Return JSON: status \"ok\", service \"PicoD\", version \"0.0.1\", uptime string\n327: \n328: 9. **Path Sanitization**\n329:    - `sanitizePath` function\n330:    - Resolve workspace symlinks\n331:    - Clean and join path\n332:    - Check `filepath.Rel` for `..` escape\n333:    - Re-validate if path exists (follow symlinks)\n334: \n335: 10. **Tests**\n336:     - Execute: valid command, timeout, invalid timeout, empty command, working directory, env augmentation\n337:     - Files: multipart upload, JSON Base64 upload, invalid Base64, list success, list missing path, download success, path escape, not a file\n338:     - Auth: missing header, invalid format, expired JWT, non-RSA method\n339:     - Health: unauthenticated access\n340: \n341: ## References\n342: \n343: - `code-execution/spec.md` — PicoD requirements and scenarios\n344: - `code-execution/design.md` — Implementation details from reference repo\n345: - `deployment/client-go.md` — Kubernetes client for sandbox pod configuration\n346: - `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go` — `AuthModePicoD` constant\n347: - `pkg/router/jwt.go` — Router JWT issuance (key pair generation)\n348: - `docker/Dockerfile.picod` — Container build for PicoD\n349: - [github.com/gin-gonic/gin](https://github.com/gin-gonic/gin)\n350: - [github.com/golang-jwt/jwt](https://github.com/golang-jwt/jwt)\n\n(End of file - total 350 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-015 — PicoD 命令执行 API Proposal\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement PicoD (Pico Daemon), an HTTP daemon that runs inside sandbox pods to provide secure command execution and file management within a configurable workspace jail. This enables AI agents and code interpreters to execute shell commands and manage workspace files through a JWT-protected REST API.\n\n**Current State**: PicoD implementation does not exist in the codebase. The `pkg/picod` package is empty/missing, and `cmd/picod` entrypoint is not defined.\n\n**Target State**: Fully functional PicoD daemon with:\n- `POST /api/execute` — Execute shell commands with timeout, working directory, and environment control\n- `POST /api/files` — Upload files (multipart or JSON/Base64)\n- `GET /api/files?path=...` — List directory contents\n- `GET /api/files/*path` — Download files\n- `GET /health` — Unauthenticated health endpoint\n- JWT RS256 authentication via `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` environment variable\n- Workspace jail with path traversal protection\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-015/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775860539355,"end":1775860539371}}}}
