{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775860542169,"sessionID":"ses_28677de79ffe7N05If9ptgu39F","part":{"id":"prt_d79896ad60012vFY2BV4PcbW6X","messageID":"msg_d7989601a0011Zc4aSV9zb6Tcy","sessionID":"ses_28677de79ffe7N05If9ptgu39F","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775860721384,"sessionID":"ses_28677de79ffe7N05If9ptgu39F","part":{"id":"prt_d798c2663001QxJiDmCRkf3LA2","messageID":"msg_d7989601a0011Zc4aSV9zb6Tcy","sessionID":"ses_28677de79ffe7N05If9ptgu39F","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-a54f407855d242c0a95315c42e458973","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-015/design.md","content":"# AR-015 — PicoD 命令执行 API Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-015 — PicoD 命令执行 API |\n| Module | `pkg/picod` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\nPicoD (Pico Daemon) is an HTTP daemon that runs inside sandbox pods to provide secure command execution and file management within a configurable workspace jail. It exposes REST APIs protected by RS256 JWT authentication, enabling AI agents and code interpreters to execute shell commands and manage workspace files with timeout control, path traversal protection, and workspace jail enforcement.\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### System Context\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                     Kubernetes Cluster                               │\n│  ┌─────────────┐     ┌─────────────┐     ┌─────────────────────────┐│\n│  │   Router    │────▶│  Workload   │────▶│      Sandbox Pod        ││\n│  │ Deployment  │     │   Manager   │     │ ┌─────────────────────┐ ││\n│  │             │     │             │     │ │      PicoD          │ ││\n│  │ JWTManager  │     │ Creates     │     │ │  ┌───────────────┐  │ ││\n│  │ (Private    │     │ Pod +       │     │ │  │ AuthManager   │  │ ││\n│  │  Key)       │     │ Inject      │     │ │  │ (Public Key)  │  │ ││\n│  │             │     │ Public Key  │     │ │  └───────────────┘  │ ││\n│  │             │     │ via Env Var │     │ │  ┌───────────────┐  │ ││\n│  │             │     │             │     │ │  │ Execute API   │  │ ││\n│  │             │     │             │     │ │  │ Files API     │  │ ││\n│  │             │     │             │     │ │  │ Health API    │  │ ││\n│  │             │     │             │     │ │  └───────────────┘  │ ││\n│  │             │     │             │     │ │      Workspace      │ ││\n│  │             │     │             │     │ │      (Jail Root)    │ ││\n│  └─────────────┘     └─────────────┘     │ └─────────────────────┘ ││\n│         │                                 └─────────────────────────┘│\n│         │ JWT Token (RS256)                                          │\n│         ▼                                                            │\n│  ┌─────────────┐                                                    │\n│  │   Client    │────▶ Router Proxy ────▶ PicoD /api/*              │\n│  │  (SDK/CLI)  │                                                    │\n│  └─────────────┘                                                    │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Component Diagram\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                         PicoD Server                                 │\n│ ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌───────────────────────────┐ │\n│ │   Config    │  │   AuthManager   │  │      Gin Engine           │ │\n│ │ ┌─────────┐ │  │ ┌─────────────┐ │  │ ┌─────────────────────────┐│ │\n│ │ │ Port    │ │  │ │ publicKey   │ │  │ │ Logger Middleware       ││ │\n│ │ │Workspace│ │  │ │ mutex       │ │  │ │ Recovery Middleware     ││ │\n│ │ └─────────┘ │  │ └─────────────┘ │  │ │                         ││ │\n│ └─────────────┘  │ AuthMiddleware  │  │ │ /health (no auth)       ││ │\n│                  │ LoadPublicKey   │  │ │                         ││ │\n│                  └─────────────────┘  │ │ /api (JWT auth)         ││ │\n│                                       │ │   /execute              ││ │\n│                                       │ │   /files                ││ │\n│                                       │ │   /files/*path          ││ │\n│                                       │ └─────────────────────────┐│ │\n│                                       └───────────────────────────┘ │\n│ ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n│ │                      sanitizePath                                │ │\n│ │   Workspace Jail: symlink resolution, path traversal prevention │ │\n│ └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n│ ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n│ │                   exec.CommandContext                            │ │\n│ │   Timeout enforcement, stdout/stderr capture, exit code handling │ │\n│ └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Request Flow\n\n```\nClient Request:\n┌──────────┐    ┌──────────┐    ┌───────────────────────────────────┐\n│  Client  │───▶│  Router  │───▶│            PicoD                  │\n│          │    │          │    │                                   │\n│ POST     │    │ Validate │    │ 1. AuthMiddleware:                │\n│ /api/    │    │ Session  │    │    - Extract Bearer token         │\n│ execute  │    │ Generate │    │    - Parse JWT with RS256         │\n│          │    │ JWT      │    │    - Validate expiration          │\n│          │    │          │    │    - Apply MaxBytesReader         │\n│          │    │          │    │                                   │\n│          │    │          │    │ 2. ExecuteHandler:                │\n│          │    │          │    │    - Bind ExecuteRequest          │\n│          │    │          │    │    - Parse timeout duration       │\n│          │    │          │    │    - Create context with deadline │\n│          │    │          │    │    - Sanitize working directory   │\n│          │    │          │    │    - exec.CommandContext          │\n│          │    │          │    │    - Capture stdout/stderr        │\n│          │    │          │    │    - Return ExecuteResponse       │\n└──────────┘    └──────────┘    └───────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n---\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### Config (`pkg/picod/config.go`)\n\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    Port      int    // HTTP listening port (default: 8080)\n    Workspace string // Workspace directory path (default: empty → CWD)\n}\n```\n\n### Server (`pkg/picod/server.go`)\n\n```go\ntype Server struct {\n    config      *Config               // Server configuration\n    engine      *gin.Engine           // Gin HTTP framework\n    httpServer  *http.Server          // Underlying HTTP server\n    authManager *AuthManager          // JWT authentication manager\n    workspace   string                // Resolved workspace directory (absolute path)\n    startTime   time.Time             // Server start time for uptime tracking\n}\n```\n\n### AuthManager (`pkg/picod/auth.go`)\n\n```go\ntype AuthManager struct {\n    publicKey *rsa.PublicKey  // RSA public key for JWT validation\n    mutex     sync.RWMutex    // Thread-safe public key access\n}\n```\n\n### ExecuteRequest (`pkg/picod/execute.go`)\n\n```go\ntype ExecuteRequest struct {\n    Command    []string          `json:\"command\" binding:\"required\"`     // Command array: [executable, args...]\n    Timeout    string            `json:\"timeout\"`                        // Duration string (e.g., \"30s\", \"5m\")\n    WorkingDir string            `json:\"working_dir\"`                    // Optional working directory (relative to workspace)\n    Env        map[string]string `json:\"env\"`                            // Optional environment variables\n}\n```\n\n### ExecuteResponse (`pkg/picod/execute.go`)\n\n```go\ntype ExecuteResponse struct {\n    Stdout    string    `json:\"stdout\"`     // Captured stdout content\n    Stderr    string    `json:\"stderr\"`     // Captured stderr content\n    ExitCode  int       `json:\"exit_code\"`  // Process exit code (124 for timeout)\n    Duration  float64   `json:\"duration\"`   // Execution duration in seconds\n    StartTime time.Time `json:\"start_time\"` // Command start timestamp\n    EndTime   time.Time `json:\"end_time\"`   // Command end timestamp\n}\n```\n\n### FileInfo (`pkg/picod/files.go`)\n\n```go\ntype FileInfo struct {\n    Path     string    `json:\"path\"`     // Relative path from workspace\n    Size     int64     `json:\"size\"`     // File size in bytes\n    Mode     string    `json:\"mode\"`     // File mode as octal string (e.g., \"0644\")\n    Modified time.Time `json:\"modified\"` // Last modification time\n}\n```\n\n### UploadFileRequest (`pkg/picod/files.go`)\n\n```go\ntype UploadFileRequest struct {\n    Path    string `json:\"path\" binding:\"required\"`    // Destination path (relative to workspace)\n    Content string `json:\"content\" binding:\"required\"` // Base64-encoded file content\n    Mode    string `json:\"mode\"`                       // Optional octal file mode (e.g., \"0755\")\n}\n```\n\n### FileEntry (`pkg/picod/files.go`)\n\n```go\ntype FileEntry struct {\n    Name     string    `json:\"name\"`     // Entry name (filename or directory name)\n    Size     int64     `json:\"size\"`     // Entry size in bytes\n    Modified time.Time `json:\"modified\"` // Last modification time\n    Mode     string    `json:\"mode\"`     // Entry mode as octal string\n    IsDir    bool      `json:\"is_dir\"`   // Whether entry is a directory\n}\n```\n\n### ListFilesResponse (`pkg/picod/files.go`)\n\n```go\ntype ListFilesResponse struct {\n    Files []FileEntry `json:\"files\"` // Array of file/directory entries\n    Path  string      `json:\"path\"`  // Directory path (relative to workspace)\n}\n```\n\n### Constants\n\n| Constant | Value | File | Purpose |\n|----------|-------|------|---------|\n| `TimeoutExitCode` | `124` | `execute.go` | Exit code when command exceeds timeout |\n| `MaxBodySize` | `32 << 20` (32 MiB) | `auth.go` | Request body size limit after JWT validation |\n| `PublicKeyEnvVar` | `\"PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY\"` | `auth.go` | Environment variable for PEM public key |\n| `maxFileMode` | `0777` | `files.go` | Maximum file mode permission |\n| `defaultTimeout` | `60 * time.Second` | `execute.go` | Command timeout when not specified |\n| `defaultFileMode` | `0644` | `files.go` | File mode when mode invalid/empty |\n| `readHeaderTimeout` | `10 * time.Second` | `server.go` | HTTP ReadHeaderTimeout |\n| `version` | `\"0.0.1\"` | `health.go` | PicoD version string |\n| `service` | `\"PicoD\"` | `health.go` | Service name for health response |\n\n---\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### Endpoints Summary\n\n| Endpoint | Method | Auth | Handler | Description |\n|----------|--------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `/health` | GET | No | `HealthCheckHandler` | Server health status |\n| `/api/execute` | POST | JWT | `ExecuteHandler` | Execute shell command |\n| `/api/files` | POST | JWT | `UploadFileHandler` | Upload file (multipart or JSON) |\n| `/api/files` | GET | JWT | `ListFilesHandler` | List directory contents |\n| `/api/files/*path` | GET | JWT | `DownloadFileHandler` | Download file |\n\n### Health Check\n\n**Endpoint**: `GET /health`\n\n**Authentication**: None\n\n**Response** (200 OK):\n```json\n{\n    \"status\": \"ok\",\n    \"service\": \"PicoD\",\n    \"version\": \"0.0.1\",\n    \"uptime\": \"2h30m15s\"\n}\n```\n\n### Execute Command\n\n**Endpoint**: `POST /api/execute`\n\n**Authentication**: JWT Bearer token (RS256)\n\n**Request Body**:\n```json\n{\n    \"command\": [\"python\", \"-c\", \"print('hello')\"],\n    \"timeout\": \"30s\",\n    \"working_dir\": \"subdir\",\n    \"env\": {\n        \"MY_VAR\": \"value\"\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Request Fields**:\n| Field | Type | Required | Description |\n|-------|------|----------|-------------|\n| `command` | `[]string` | Yes | Executable and arguments |\n| `timeout` | `string` | No | Duration string (default: 60s) |\n| `working_dir` | `string` | No | Working directory relative to workspace |\n| `env` | `map[string]string` | No | Environment variables to augment |\n\n**Response** (200 OK):\n```json\n{\n    \"stdout\": \"hello\\n\",\n    \"stderr\": \"\",\n    \"exit_code\": 0,\n    \"duration\": 0.523,\n    \"start_time\": \"2026-04-11T10:30:00Z\",\n    \"end_time\": \"2026-04-11T10:30:00.523Z\"\n}\n```\n\n**Error Responses**:\n- 400 Bad Request: Missing/empty command, invalid working directory (path escape)\n- 401 Unauthorized: Missing/invalid/expired JWT\n\n### Upload File (JSON)\n\n**Endpoint**: `POST /api/files`\n\n**Authentication**: JWT Bearer token (RS256)\n\n**Content-Type**: `application/json`\n\n**Request Body**:\n```json\n{\n    \"path\": \"output/result.txt\",\n    \"content\": \"SGVsbG8gV29ybGQ=\",  // Base64-encoded\n    \"mode\": \"0644\"\n}\n```\n\n**Response** (200 OK):\n```json\n{\n    \"path\": \"output/result.txt\",\n    \"size\": 11,\n    \"mode\": \"0644\",\n    \"modified\": \"2026-04-11T10:35:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\n### Upload File (Multipart)\n\n**Endpoint**: `POST /api/files`\n\n**Authentication**: JWT Bearer token (RS256)\n\n**Content-Type**: `multipart/form-data`\n\n**Form Fields**:\n| Field | Type | Required | Description |\n|-------|------|----------|-------------|\n| `path` | `string` | Yes | Destination path |\n| `file` | `file` | Yes | File content |\n| `mode` | `string` | No | Octal file mode |\n\n**Response** (200 OK): Same as JSON upload\n\n### List Files\n\n**Endpoint**: `GET /api/files?path=<directory>`\n\n**Authentication**: JWT Bearer token (RS256)\n\n**Query Parameters**:\n| Parameter | Type | Required | Description |\n|-----------|------|----------|-------------|\n| `path` | `string` | Yes | Directory path to list |\n\n**Response** (200 OK):\n```json\n{\n    \"files\": [\n        {\n            \"name\": \"src\",\n            \"size\": 4096,\n            \"modified\": \"2026-04-11T09:00:00Z\",\n            \"mode\": \"0755\",\n            \"is_dir\": true\n        },\n        {\n            \"name\": \"main.py\",\n            \"size\": 1024,\n            \"modified\": \"2026-04-11T10:00:00Z\",\n            \"mode\": \"0644\",\n            \"is_dir\": false\n        }\n    ],\n    \"path\": \"project\"\n}\n```\n\n### Download File\n\n**Endpoint**: `GET /api/files/<path>`\n\n**Authentication**: JWT Bearer token (RS256)\n\n**Path Parameter**: File path relative to workspace (wildcard capture)\n\n**Response Headers**:\n- `Content-Type`: MIME type detected from file extension\n- `Content-Disposition`: `attachment; filename=\"<filename>\"`\n\n**Response**: File content streamed directly\n\n**Error Responses**:\n- 400 Bad Request: Path traversal detected, path is directory\n- 404 Not Found: File does not exist\n\n---\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### HTTP Status Codes\n\n| Status | Condition |\n|--------|-----------|\n| 200 OK | Successful operation (including timeout exit code) |\n| 400 Bad Request | Invalid request body, missing required fields, path traversal, invalid mode |\n| 401 Unauthorized | Missing Authorization header, invalid JWT, expired token, wrong signing method |\n| 404 Not Found | File not found for download |\n| 500 Internal Server Error | Directory read failure, unexpected server error |\n\n### Error Response Format\n\n```json\n{\n    \"error\": \"<error message>\"\n}\n```\n\n### Authentication Errors\n\n| Condition | HTTP Status | Error Message |\n|-----------|-------------|---------------|\n| Missing Authorization header | 401 | `\"missing authorization header\"` |\n| Invalid token format | 401 | `\"invalid token format\"` |\n| Expired token | 401 | `\"token is expired\"` |\n| Non-RSA signing method | 401 | `\"invalid signing method\"` |\n| Invalid signature | 401 | `\"invalid signature\"` |\n\n### Execution Errors\n\n| Condition | HTTP Status | Error Message |\n|-----------|-------------|---------------|\n| Empty command array | 400 | `\"missing command\"` |\n| Invalid working directory | 400 | `\"invalid working directory: path escape detected\"` |\n| Invalid timeout format | - | Uses default 60s (no error) |\n\n### File Operation Errors\n\n| Condition | HTTP Status | Error Message |\n|-----------|-------------|---------------|\n| Missing path in list request | 400 | `\"missing path parameter\"` |\n| Path traversal detected | 400 | `\"invalid path: escape detected\"` |\n| Invalid Base64 content | 400 | `\"invalid base64 content\"` |\n| File mode > 0777 | 400 | `\"invalid file mode\"` |\n| Download path is directory | 400 | `\"path is not a file\"` |\n| File not found | 404 | `\"file not found\"` |\n| Directory read failure | 500 | `\"failed to read directory\"` |\n\n---\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests (`pkg/picod/picod_test.go`)\n\n#### Execute Handler Tests\n\n| Test Case | Input | Expected |\n|-----------|-------|----------|\n| Valid command | `{\"command\": [\"echo\", \"hello\"]}` | stdout=\"hello\\n\", exit_code=0 |\n| Empty command | `{\"command\": []}` | HTTP 400 |\n| Timeout exceeded | `{\"command\": [\"sleep\", \"10\"], \"timeout\": \"1s\"}` | exit_code=124, stderr=\"command timed out\" |\n| Invalid timeout | `{\"command\": [\"echo\"], \"timeout\": \"invalid\"}` | Uses default 60s |\n| Working directory | `{\"command\": [\"pwd\"], \"working_dir\": \"subdir\"}` | stdout shows subdir path |\n| Path escape working_dir | `{\"command\": [\"pwd\"], \"working_dir\": \"../escape\"}` | HTTP 400 |\n| Environment augmentation | `{\"command\": [\"env\"], \"env\": {\"MY_VAR\": \"test\"}}` | stdout contains MY_VAR |\n| Exit code propagation | `{\"command\": [\"sh\", \"-c\", \"exit 42\"]}` | exit_code=42 |\n\n#### Authentication Tests\n\n| Test Case | Input | Expected |\n|-----------|-------|----------|\n| Missing header | No Authorization | HTTP 401, \"missing authorization header\" |\n| Invalid format | `Authorization: InvalidFormat` | HTTP 401 |\n| Expired token | JWT with expired `exp` | HTTP 401, \"token is expired\" |\n| HS256 token | JWT signed with HS256 | HTTP 401, \"invalid signing method\" |\n| Valid RS256 token | JWT signed with matching public key | Request proceeds |\n\n#### File Upload Tests\n\n| Test Case | Input | Expected |\n|-----------|-------|----------|\n| Multipart upload | form-data with path, file | HTTP 200, FileInfo returned |\n| JSON Base64 upload | `{\"path\": \"test.txt\", \"content\": \"SGVsbG8=\"}` | HTTP 200, FileInfo returned |\n| Invalid Base64 | `{\"path\": \"test.txt\", \"content\": \"!!invalid\"}` | HTTP 400 |\n| Path escape | `{\"path\": \"../escape.txt\", \"content\": \"test\"}` | HTTP 400 |\n| Invalid mode | `{\"path\": \"test.txt\", \"content\": \"test\", \"mode\": \"9999\"}` | Uses default 0644 |\n| Mode > 0777 | `{\"path\": \"test.txt\", \"content\": \"test\", \"mode\": \"1000\"}` | HTTP 400 |\n| Parent directory creation | `{\"path\": \"new/dir/file.txt\", \"content\": \"test\"}` | Parents created with 0755 |\n\n#### File List Tests\n\n| Test Case | Input | Expected |\n|-----------|-------|----------|\n| List valid directory | `GET /api/files?path=subdir` | HTTP 200, FileEntry array |\n| Missing path parameter | `GET /api/files` | HTTP 400 |\n| Path escape | `GET /api/files?path=../escape` | HTTP 400 |\n| Non-existent directory | `GET /api/files?path=nonexistent` | HTTP 500 |\n\n#### File Download Tests\n\n| Test Case | Input | Expected |\n|-----------|-------|----------|\n| Download existing file | `GET /api/files/existing.txt` | HTTP 200, file content |\n| Leading slash stripped | `GET /api/files//absolute.txt` | Resolved correctly |\n| Path escape | `GET /api/files/../escape.txt` | HTTP 400 |\n| File not found | `GET /api/files/nonexistent.txt` | HTTP 404 |\n| Path is directory | `GET /api/files/subdir` | HTTP 400, \"path is not a file\" |\n\n#### Path Sanitization Tests\n\n| Test Case | Input | Expected |\n|-----------|-------|----------|\n| Valid relative path | `\"subdir/file.txt\"` | Absolute path within workspace |\n| Absolute path | `\"/workspace/file.txt\"` | Strips leading `/`, resolves within workspace |\n| Path traversal | `\"../escape.txt\"` | Error: path escape detected |\n| Deep traversal | `\"subdir/../../escape.txt\"` | Error: path escape detected |\n| Symlink escape | Symlink pointing outside workspace | Error after resolution |\n| Null byte injection | `\"file%00.txt\"` | Cleaned, safe path |\n\n#### Health Check Tests\n\n| Test Case | Input | Expected |\n|-----------|-------|----------|\n| Unauthenticated access | `GET /health` (no JWT) | HTTP 200, status=\"ok\" |\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n| Test Scenario | Description |\n|---------------|-------------|\n| Full execute flow | Router generates JWT → Client calls PicoD → Command executes |\n| File lifecycle | Upload file → List directory → Download file → Verify content |\n| Auth key mismatch | Router uses different key pair → PicoD rejects token |\n| Timeout enforcement | Long-running command killed at deadline |\n\n### Test Helper Requirements\n\n```go\nfunc setupTestServer(t *testing.T) *Server\nfunc generateTestJWT(publicKey *rsa.PublicKey) string\nfunc createTestWorkspace(t *testing.T) string\nfunc cleanupTestWorkspace(t *testing.T, path string)\n```\n\n---\n\n## File Structure\n\n```\npkg/picod/\n├── config.go           # Config struct definition\n├── server.go           # Server struct, NewServer, Run, route registration\n├── auth.go             # AuthManager, NewAuthManager, LoadPublicKeyFromEnv, AuthMiddleware\n├── execute.go          # ExecuteRequest, ExecuteResponse, ExecuteHandler, constants\n├── files.go            # FileInfo, UploadFileRequest, FileEntry, ListFilesResponse, file handlers\n├── health.go           # HealthCheckHandler, version constant\n├── sanitize.go         # sanitizePath function for workspace jail security\n├── picod_test.go       # Unit tests for all handlers\n└── doc.go              # Package documentation\n\ncmd/picod/\n└── main.go             # Entry point with CLI flag parsing, klog initialization\n```\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Package | Version | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | v1.10+ | HTTP framework, route registration, middleware, JSON binding |\n| `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | v5.2+ | JWT parsing, RSA signing method validation, leeway/expiry options |\n| `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Existing | CLI flag registration, structured logging, fatal error handling |\n| `crypto/rsa` | Standard | RSA public key type |\n| `crypto/x509` | Standard | PKIX public key parsing |\n| `encoding/pem` | Standard | PEM block decoding |\n| `encoding/base64` | Standard | Base64 decoding for JSON file upload |\n| `os/exec` | Standard | `exec.CommandContext` for command execution |\n| `path/filepath` | Standard | Path cleaning, symlink resolution, relative path computation |\n| `mime` | Standard | `mime.TypeByExtension` for download Content-Type |\n| `strconv` | Standard | `ParseUint` for octal file mode parsing |\n| `sync` | Standard | `sync.RWMutex` for thread-safe public key access |\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n### Server Initialization Flow\n\n1. **main.go**:\n   - `flag.Set(\"logtostderr\", \"true\")` — Enable klog to stderr\n   - `klog.InitFlags(nil)` — Register klog flags\n   - Define `-port` flag (default 8080)\n   - Define `-workspace` flag (default empty)\n   - `flag.Parse()` — Parse all flags\n   - Create `Config` from flag values\n   - Call `NewServer(config)` — Fatal on error\n   - Call `server.Run(ctx)` — Start HTTP server\n   - Log startup: `klog.InfoS(\"PicoD started\", \"port\", port, \"workspace\", workspace)`\n\n2. **NewServer**:\n   - Initialize `engine` with `gin.New()`\n   - Set `gin.ReleaseMode` for production\n   - Apply `gin.Logger()` and `gin.Recovery()` middleware\n   - Resolve workspace:\n     - If `Config.Workspace` empty: `os.Getwd()`\n     - If relative: `filepath.Abs(workspace)`\n   - Initialize `AuthManager`:\n     - Load public key from `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` env var\n     - Fatal if missing or invalid PEM\n   - Store `startTime = time.Now()`\n   - Configure `http.Server`:\n     - `Addr = fmt.Sprintf(\":%d\", config.Port)`\n     - `Handler = engine`\n     - `ReadHeaderTimeout = 10 * time.Second`\n   - Register routes\n   - Return `*Server`\n\n### Route Registration Pattern\n\n```go\nengine.GET(\"/health\", s.HealthCheckHandler)\n\napi := engine.Group(\"/api\")\napi.Use(s.authManager.AuthMiddleware())\n{\n    api.POST(\"/execute\", s.ExecuteHandler)\n    api.POST(\"/files\", s.UploadFileHandler)\n    api.GET(\"/files\", s.ListFilesHandler)\n    api.GET(\"/files/*path\", s.DownloadFileHandler)\n}\n```\n\n### JWT Validation Flow\n\n1. Extract `Authorization` header\n2. Strip `Bearer ` prefix (case-sensitive)\n3. Parse token with options:\n   - `jwt.WithExpirationRequired()`\n   - `jwt.WithIssuedAt()`\n   - `jwt.WithLeeway(time.Minute)`\n4. Validate signing method:\n   - Type-assert to `*jwt.SigningMethodRSA`\n   - Reject HS256 and other non-RSA methods\n5. Verify signature with public key\n6. On success: Apply `http.MaxBytesReader(w, r.Body, MaxBodySize)`\n\n### Path Sanitization Algorithm\n\n```go\nfunc sanitizePath(workspace, requestedPath string) (string, error) {\n    // 1. Resolve workspace directory (follow symlinks)\n    resolvedWorkspace, err := filepath.EvalSymlinks(workspace)\n    if err != nil {\n        return \"\", err\n    }\n    \n    // 2. Clean requested path\n    cleaned := filepath.Clean(requestedPath)\n    \n    // 3. Strip leading \"/\" if absolute\n    cleaned = strings.TrimPrefix(cleaned, \"/\")\n    \n    // 4. Join with workspace\n    candidate := filepath.Join(resolvedWorkspace, cleaned)\n    \n    // 5. Check for traversal\n    rel, err := filepath.Rel(resolvedWorkspace, candidate)\n    if err != nil {\n        return \"\", err\n    }\n    if strings.HasPrefix(rel, \"..\") {\n        return \"\", errors.New(\"path escape detected\")\n    }\n    \n    // 6. If path exists, re-validate after symlink resolution\n    if _, err := os.Stat(candidate); err == nil {\n        resolved, err := filepath.EvalSymlinks(candidate)\n        if err != nil {\n            return \"\", err\n        }\n        rel, err := filepath.Rel(resolvedWorkspace, resolved)\n        if err != nil || strings.HasPrefix(rel, \"..\") {\n            return \"\", errors.New(\"path escape detected after symlink resolution\")\n        }\n        return resolved, nil\n    }\n    \n    return candidate, nil\n}\n```\n\n### Command Execution Pattern\n\n```go\nfunc (s *Server) ExecuteHandler(c *gin.Context) {\n    var req ExecuteRequest\n    if err := c.ShouldBindJSON(&req); err != nil {\n        c.JSON(400, gin.H{\"error\": \"invalid request body\"})\n        return\n    }\n    \n    if len(req.Command) == 0 {\n        c.JSON(400, gin.H{\"error\": \"missing command\"})\n        return\n    }\n    \n    // Parse timeout (default 60s on invalid)\n    timeout := defaultTimeout\n    if req.Timeout != \"\" {\n        parsed, err := time.ParseDuration(req.Timeout)\n        if err == nil {\n            timeout = parsed\n        }\n    }\n    \n    // Create context with deadline\n    ctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(c.Request.Context(), timeout)\n    defer cancel()\n    \n    // Build command\n    cmd := exec.CommandContext(ctx, req.Command[0], req.Command[1:]...)\n    \n    // Sanitize working directory\n    if req.WorkingDir != \"\" {\n        sanitized, err := sanitizePath(s.workspace, req.WorkingDir)\n        if err != nil {\n            c.JSON(400, gin.H{\"error\": \"invalid working directory\"})\n            return\n        }\n        cmd.Dir = sanitized\n    } else {\n        cmd.Dir = s.workspace\n    }\n    \n    // Augment environment\n    if req.Env != nil {\n        cmd.Env = os.Environ()\n        for k, v := range req.Env {\n            cmd.Env = append(cmd.Env, fmt.Sprintf(\"%s=%s\", k, v))\n        }\n    }\n    \n    // Capture output\n    stdout, stderr := &bytes.Buffer{}, &bytes.Buffer{}\n    cmd.Stdout = stdout\n    cmd.Stderr = stderr\n    cmd.Stdin = nil\n    \n    // Execute\n    startTime := time.Now()\n    err := cmd.Run()\n    endTime := time.Now()\n    \n    // Handle timeout\n    exitCode := 0\n    if err != nil {\n        if ctx.Err() == context.DeadlineExceeded {\n            exitCode = TimeoutExitCode\n            stderr.WriteString(\"command timed out\")\n        } else if exitErr, ok := err.(*exec.ExitError); ok {\n            exitCode = exitErr.ExitCode()\n        } else {\n            exitCode = 1\n        }\n    }\n    \n    c.JSON(200, ExecuteResponse{\n        Stdout:    stdout.String(),\n        Stderr:    stderr.String(),\n        ExitCode:  exitCode,\n        Duration:  endTime.Sub(startTime).Seconds(),\n        StartTime: startTime,\n        EndTime:   endTime,\n    })\n}\n```\n\n### File Mode Parsing\n\n```go\nfunc parseFileMode(modeStr string) (os.FileMode, error) {\n    if modeStr == \"\" {\n        return defaultFileMode, nil\n    }\n    \n    mode, err := strconv.ParseUint(modeStr, 8, 32)\n    if err != nil {\n        return defaultFileMode, nil // Invalid → use default\n    }\n    \n    if mode > maxFileMode {\n        return 0, errors.New(\"invalid file mode\")\n    }\n    \n    return os.FileMode(mode), nil\n}\n```\n\n### JWT Key Compatibility with Router\n\nPicoD validates tokens issued by `pkg/router/jwt.go`:\n\n| Router Component | PicoD Requirement |\n|------------------|-------------------|\n| `JWTManager.privateKey` | RSA 2048-bit, RS256 signing |\n| `encodePublicKeyPEM` | PKIX format (`PUBLIC KEY` block) |\n| `GetPublicKeyPEM()` | Injected as `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` env var |\n| `jwtIssuer` | Not validated by PicoD (optional) |\n| `RouterClaims` | Custom claims not validated by PicoD (only signature/expiry) |\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- `changes/AR-015/delta-spec.md` — GIVEN/WHEN/THEN scenarios\n- `changes/AR-015/proposal.md` — Proposal and alternatives analysis\n- `deployment/client-go.md` — Kubernetes client for sandbox pod configuration\n- `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types.go` — `AuthModePicoD` constant\n- `pkg/router/jwt.go` — Router JWT issuance (key pair generation, PEM encoding)\n- `pkg/router/errors.go` — Router error types pattern\n- `pkg/workloadmanager/server.go` — HTTP server lifecycle pattern\n- `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go` — Error handling pattern\n- [github.com/gin-gonic/gin](https://github.com/gin-gonic/gin) — Gin framework\n- [github.com/golang-jwt/jwt](https://github.com/golang-jwt/jwt) — JWT library"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/router/server.go\">\nERROR [10:2] error while importing github.com/gin-gonic/gin: missing go.sum entry for module providing package golang.org/x/crypto/sha3 (imported by github.com/go-playground/validator/v10); to add:\n\tgo get github.com/go-playground/validator/v10@v10.20.0\nERROR [10:2] error while importing github.com/gin-gonic/gin: missing go.sum entry for module providing package golang.org/x/net/html (imported by github.com/gabriel-vasile/mimetype/internal/charset); to add:\n\tgo get github.com/gabriel-vasile/mimetype/internal/charset@v1.4.3\nERROR [10:2] error while importing github.com/gin-gonic/gin: missing go.sum entry for module providing package golang.org/x/net/http2/h2c (imported by github.com/gin-gonic/gin); to add:\n\tgo get github.com/gin-gonic/gin@v1.10.0\nERROR [10:2] error while importing github.com/gin-gonic/gin: missing go.sum entry for module providing package golang.org/x/text/language (imported by github.com/go-playground/validator/v10); to add:\n\tgo get github.com/go-playground/validator/v10@v10.20.0\n</diagnostics>\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox_delete_test.go\">\nERROR [17:2] error while importing